Emergency services assist injured sailor Picture: Supplied A sailor was injured aboard the container vessel M/V Thuringa which was sailing towards Hong Kong on Wednesday afternoon. The 42-year-old Chinese sailor was reportedly struck by sheet metal on the chest from an accident on board where it is believed that the sheet metal shifted and fell onto him and he was trapped underneath the metal, unconscious with breathing difficulties. The vessel had to diverted and head towards the Port Elizabeth harbor following the incident. The doctor on duty requested NSRI and rescue paramedics to be dispatched immediately and the injured sailor to be taken to hospital as soon as possible. The EMS rescue paramedic, assisted by NSRI medics, treated the sailor on board and his condition was stabilised. He was transported to hospital by the EMS ambulance in a serious but stable condition. &nbsp; Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share